The cathode is, of course, an “air cathode” and performs the reduction of O2 to complete the redox reaction of the battery. Being a gas electrode, the cathode has to be porous and electrocatalytically active. The cathodic electrochemical reaction can be written as follows:5O2+2H2O+4e-→4OH-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
